:image/svg+xml;base64,PHN2ZyB4bWxucz0iaHR0cDovL3d3dy53My5vcmcvMjAwMC9zdmciIHdpZHRoPSIzMDAiIGhlaWdodD0iMTkwIiB2aWV3Qm94PSIwIDAgMzAwIDE5MCI+PHJlY3Qgd2lkdGg9IjEwMCUiIGhlaWdodD0iMTAwJSIgZmlsbD0iI2NmZDRkYiIvPjwvc3ZnPg==\" loading=\"lazy\" class=\"screenshot\" data-src=\"https://lowendbox.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/07/Host1Plus-Web_Hosting_Services_Provided_by_HOST1PLUS_-_2014-07-19_17.28.30-300x190.png.webp\" alt=\"Host1Plus-Web_Hosting_Services_Provided_by_HOST1PLUS_-_2014-07-19_17.28.30\" width=\"300\" height=\"190\"></a>Paulius, from <a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Host1Plus.com,</a> is back with an exclusive offer for 20% off their regular price by using the coupon <strong>LEB</strong>. This coupon expires September 30th, so order a server while the coupon is still valid!</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Bronze</strong><p></p><ul><li>256MB RAM</li><li>0.5 vCPU Core</li><li>20GB HDD space</li><li>500GB traffic</li><li>50Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/Custom</li><li>Coupon: <strong>LEB</strong></li><li><del>$2.00/month</del></li><li>$1.60/month</li><li><a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/vps-hosting/?utm_source=lowbox&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=article\">Order here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Silver</strong><p></p><ul><li>512MB RAM</li><li>1 vCPU Core</li><li>30GB HDD space</li><li>1TB traffic</li><li>50Mbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/Custom</li><li>Coupon: <strong>LEB</strong></li><li><del>$5/month</del></li><li>$4/month</li><li><a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/vps-hosting/?utm_source=lowbox&amp;utm_medium=link&amp;utm_campaign=article\">Order here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p><strong>Some notes</strong>: <em>you get a small additional discount of you order for a longer billing term. Bandwidth and pricing may vary in Brazil. Additional IPv4 are available for $2/month.</em></p><p>Since Host1Plus have overhauled their plans, TUN/TAP, NAT, and PPP are all included free of charge. I\u2019m still sure this is the cheapest South Africa offer we\u2019ve ever seen on LowEndBox.com, the second host in it\u2019s history that features that location, and I think there\u2019s not too many competition to be expected. I think they are the only host we\u2019ve featured thus far that offers a Brazil location. What makes these offer even more unique, is that it has quite some bandwidth. Yes, the port speed may be limited to 50Mbps, but 500GB or 1TB of bandwidth is still a lot for these locations. Los Angeles was recently added as a location, so people based in Asia can order from there as well to get reduced latency. Host1Plus has been doing business since 2008 and is a division of D. E. Technologies Ltd., which is a registered company in England and Wales. They have offices in London (UK), Kaunas (Lithuania), Frankfurt am Maine (Germany), and Sao Paolo (Brazil) so I have the idea they have quite an operation running. From my personal experience I can say these machines run just fine. I have one both in Brazil and South Africa and for the past 11 months they\u2019ve had 100% uptime. If you decide to give them a try, please share your experiences with us in the comments!<br>\n<span id=\"more-5755\"></span></p><p>HOST1PLUS accepts payments via Debit/Credit card, PayPal, AliPay, WebMoney, CashU, and Paysera. They have a <a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/refund-policy/\" target=\"_blank\">refund policy</a> which is worth reading before you order, so you know what you\u2019re up to. Their <a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/terms-of-service/\">Terms of Service</a> has a long list of prohibited content and actions, such as copyright infringing content, use of gaming servers, proxies, bots, etc. Be sure to also read their <a href=\"http://www.host1plus.com/anti-spam-policy/\">Spam Policy</a>.</p><p><strong>Network information</strong></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Frankfurt am Main, Germany</span><br>\nIPv4 test: 5.175.192.201</p><